      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'When electric current flows into the motor, it enters through the brushes.

    The
    current passes through the commutator and into the armature windings.


    The
    magnetic field from the stator interacts with the magnetic field in the rotor.

    This
    interaction creates torque and causes the rotor to spin.


    The spinning rotor
    turns the shaft.

    The shaft delivers mechanical energy to an external load.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
